        "schemeImageUrl": "",
        "detailedDescription_md": "The scheme &amp;quot;Mukhyamantri Gyansetu Merit Scholarship Yojana&amp;quot; by the Education Department, Government of Gujarat aims to select 30,000 brilliant students who have completed their Class 5 education consecutively in government, aided, or RTE-approved schools and provide them with scholarships to study in selected government, aided, or private schools from Class 6th to Class 12th. The selection is done through a Common Entrance Test conducted by the State Examination Board, Gandhinagar.\n<br>\n\n",
        "benefits_md": "> **Government Schools and Government -aided Schools (Approved by Education Department):**\n\n\n\n  - For Class 6th to 8th: ₹5,000/- per year.\n  - For Class 9th to 10th: ₹6,000/- per year.\n  - For Class 11th to 12th: ₹7,000/- per year.\n\n\n> **Private (Selected) Schools:**\n\n\n\n  - For Class 6th to 8th: ₹20,000/- per year.\n  - For Class 9th to 10th: ₹22,000/- per year.\n  - For Class 11th to 12th: ₹25,000/- per year.\n\n\n> **Frequency of Disbursement:** \n\n\n\n  - Disbursed annually in two installments; the first 50% is given after confirmation of at least 80% attendance in the first semester.\n\n\n<br>\n\n",
        "briefDescription": "This scheme introduced by the Education Department, Government of Gujarat, aims to support meritorious students by providing scholarships from Class 6th to Class 12th in selected schools.",
        "exclusions_md": "",
